---
// /atelier/archive/cockpit — the RETIRED cockpit surface (ADR 0008: surfaces are archived,
// not deleted). The old URL /atelier/cockpit 301s here (public/_redirects). The atlas that
// used to live inside it has moved to /atelier/material.
// HONESTY (P0.6, 16.07.): this is a retired INTERFACE rendered against the CURRENT archive —
// CockpitPage reads the gate-synced engine JSONs (atlas/rhizome/vital-signs) and the live
// works collection, so its numbers can still move when the archive does. The banner says so;
// do not label it a frozen snapshot unless the data is actually pinned. Since Protocol v4
// (2026-07-18) the nightly session cadence itself is history — the closure/vital-signs
// metrics are the nightly phase's own instrument, kept as a dated artefact.
import Page from '@/layouts/Page.astro'
import CockpitPage from '@/components/pages/CockpitPage.astro'
const locale = 'en' as const
---
<Page
  title="Cockpit (archived) — Error as Method | Frank Bültge"
  description="Archived surface from the nightly phase (28 June – 18 July 2026): a breathing closure ring, the rhizome of works, and the Atlas as its outside — kept as a dated artefact."
>
  <div class="mx-auto mt-8 w-full max-w-6xl px-4">
    <p class="rounded-lg border border-line bg-panel px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs text-fg-muted">
      Retired interface (ADR 0008) — no longer the entrance, rendered against the current
      Atelier archive. It was the instrument of the nightly phase (28 June – 18 July 2026);
      since Protocol v4 the practice works in bounded projects, and these numbers only move
      when the archive itself does.
      The atlas now lives in <a href="/atelier/material" class="underline hover:text-fg">material</a> ·
      <a href="/atelier" class="underline hover:text-fg">back to the sheet →</a>
    </p>
  </div>
  <CockpitPage locale={locale} />
</Page>
